06-08 June - Cooked Cream 

- 1/2 cup scalded milk
- 1/2 cup sugar 
- 1/4 cup flour
- 3-4 well beaten eggs OR 2 eggs and 2 yolks

In a double boiler mix milk, sugar, and flour together. Beat eggs until light and then add scalded milk gradually until well blended. Cook stirring constantly until thickens. Remove from heat and continue to stir to release steam. Cool mixture before filling pastry. Add 1/4-3/4 cup whipped cream for enrichment. 